0:As he walked cautiously through the narrow, trash-ridden streets of Maruyamacho, Ban Yasuji jammed one hand inside his pants pocket.\p;
100:Inside, he found a few dozen small coins.\p;
200:〔Suwa〕“Sir, what exactly are you expecting to find at the Cruc-affixion crime scene?”\p;
300:〔Suwa〕“It's already been more than two weeks since it happened. Don't you think it's been investigated well enough?”\p;
400:〔Suwa〕“With all due respect, new evidence isn't just gonna pop out of thin air.”\p;
500:His partner, Detective Suwa, had been walking behind him, grousing in an irritated voice for quite some time.\p;
600:That was understandable, of course, as the job originally assigned to them had been to tail an important witness for the New Gen cases—Nishijou Takumi.\p;
700:However, the two of them had abandoned their tailing mission, and had instead come to the scene of the third New Gen incident—colloquially known as the “Cruc-affixion.”\p;
800:Ban had decided to abandon their original task of tailing Nishijou Takumi, forcing the burden onto some other detective in the same jurisdiction.\p;
900:The rookie detective, Suwa, was not pleased by this.\p;
1000:〔Suwa〕“C'mon, there's no way this'll pan out. Let's just go back to tailing already.”\p;
1100:The rookie detective had consistently been pushed around by his senior without any explanation, and he could not stand it.\p;
1200:For that reason, he had been insistently trying to persuade Ban for a long while now. But to this, Ban only said...\p;
1300:〔Ban〕“Oh, quit your yapping and follow me.”\p;
1400:He remained aloof and refused to heed his junior's perfectly sound arguments.\p;
1500:Finally, they at last came across a narrow road, blocked off by yellow barricade tape.\p;
1600:As Suwa let out the latest in his myriad of sighs, his cell phone began vibrating near his chest.\p;
1700:He quickly took out his phone—which had been set to vibrate—assumed the look of a capable detective, and pressed the accept button.\p;
1800:〔Suwa〕“Suwa here.”\p;
1900:〔Suwa〕“Yes. ...Yes.”\p;
2000:As he listened to Suwa's voice coming from behind him, Ban came to a stop in front of the barricade tape.\p;
2100:Behind that tape was the crime scene.\p;
2200:A deep darkness had settled over the area, just as it had when the crime had been committed.\p;
2300:But now, there were no remaining traces of the incident—save for the barricade tape.\p;
2400:〔Suwa〕“You lost him?!”\p;
2500:〔Suwa〕“A girl...? Looks like they got us...”\p;
2600:〔Suwa〕“...All right, then go ahead and head back to his house in Shinsen.”\p;
2700:〔Suwa〕“...Yes. Make sure to keep your eyes peeled.”\p;
2800:〔Suwa〕“...No, don't worry. Assistant Inspector Ban will take all the flak for you.”\p;
2900:Ban smiled wryly upon hearing that. Suwa could be surprisingly shrewd.\p;
3000:Of course, Ban had no intention of placing the blame onto his subordinates, nor onto the detective he had placed in charge.\p;
3100:〔Suwa〕“We'll join up with you as soon as we're done here. Really sorry about all this. Good luck.”\p;
3200:Right as Suwa hung up the phone and returned his begrudging gaze to Ban, Ban ducked under the tape. Suwa had no choice but to reluctantly accompany him.\p;
3300:〔Ban〕“They lost him, eh?”\p;
3400:〔Suwa〕“He figured out he was being tailed.”\p;
3500:〔Suwa〕“Seems like there'd been some commotion at an Internet café a bit before that.”\p;
3600:〔Ban〕“And the girl?”\p;
3700:〔Suwa〕“Kishimoto Ayase.”\p;
3800:〔Ban〕“Ah, the little lady from the band that's been causin' us a whole host of trouble. What's the connection between 'em?”\p;
